'''hyp·na·gog·ic''' also '''hyp·no·gog·ic'''<br>
adj.<br>
1. Inducing [[sleep]]; [[soporific]].<br>
2. Of, relating to, or occurring in the state of intermediate [[consciousness]] preceding sleep: [[hypnagogic]] [[hallucinations]].<br>
3. Relating to the images or [[hallucinations]] sometimes perceived during this state.<br>
<br>
<br>
[[[French]] [[hypnagogique]] : [[Greek]] hupnos, sleep; see hypno- + [[Greek]] aggos, leading (from agein, to lead. See ag- in [[Indo-European]] Roots).]